This paper is primarily focused on object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a new architecture for modeling instance-level context and object-object relationships, which involves memory and reasoning, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves spatial reasoning, which is relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and natural language processing (cs.CL) where spatial relationships are important.
